results.description:
White Rock lake, pool behind the lower spillway steps
The Girls
A female green-winged teal & a female mallard were feeding side by side.  There is quite a size difference.  This was my first female green-winged teal.
Both are "dabbling ducks".  Both quite lovely in their own way.  Green-winged teal are the smallest dabbling duck in North America.
